svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104rzp1665703134110.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rzp1665703134110.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rzp1665703134110.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rzp1665703134110\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"rzp1665703134110__ugetuopenflag_404161\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Get the address of the flag that specifies the validity of the Oracle Logon Data Area (LDA).\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"rzp1665703134110__topic_d120923e1_d120924e1_d120925e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" id=\"rzp1665703134110__codeblock_v1x_4r1_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">unsigned char* ugetulda ();</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rzp1665703134110__topic_d85902e1_d85903e1_d85904e1_d85905e1_d85906e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1092663e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rzp1665703134110__d6420e20\">None</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rzp1665703134110__topic_d85907e1_d85908e1_d85909e1_d85910e1_d85911e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1092663e70\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rzp1665703134110__p_d120938e1_d120939e1_d120940e1\">A pointer to an <code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char</code> variable that contains the status.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rzp1665703134110__topic_d85912e1_d85913e1_d85914e1_d85915e1_d85916e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1092663e82\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rzp1665703134110__d7343e20\">Oracle only, <code class=\"ph codeph\">uora</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">NN</var> (your currently used Oracle driver).</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rzp1665703134110__topic_d85917e1_d85918e1_d85919e1_d85920e1_d85921e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1092663e98\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rzp1665703134110__p_d120950e1_d120951e1_d120952e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">ugetuopenflag</code> returns a pointer to\n            an <code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char</code> variable that contains the validity of the Oracle LDA\n            returned by <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugetulda</code>. If that variable is 1 (one), the LDA returned by\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugetulda</code> is valid; if it is zero, the LDA is invalid and should not\n            be used.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"rzp1665703134110__note_ovm_rr1_1wb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> You should always call this function before using\n            the LDA returned by <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugetulda</code> in Oracle OCI calls. If you fail to do so,\n            you might be using an invalid LDA, which is likely to produce unexpected results.\n            Obviously, you can call this function only when an Oracle driver is available to your\n            application.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rzp1665703134110__section_pvm_rr1_1wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1092663e124\">Example: ugetulda and ugetuopenflag</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following 3GL code drops the table FOOBAR from the current Oracle\n            database. Functionally, this might not be the best example, but it is simple and serves\n            to illustrate the use of <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugetulda</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugetuopenflag</code>.\n            The routine DROPTABLE can be called, using <code class=\"ph codeph\">perform</code> or\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">activate</code>, once the application has logged on to Oracle.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104rzp1665703134110_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"rzp1665703134110__codeblock_qqv_sr1_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;\n#include &lt;ocidem.h&gt;\n\nEXPORT void DROPTABLE ()\n{\nunsigned char *pflg;\nLda_Def *plda;\nCda_Def cda;\n\npflg = ugetuopenflag();\nif ( *pflg != 1 )\n{\nprintf(\"No valid LDA\\n\");\nreturn;\n}\n\nplda = (Lda_Def*)ugetulda();\n\nif ( oopen(&amp;cda, plda, NULL, -1, -1, NULL, -1) )\n{\nprintf(\"Open cursor failed\\n\");\nreturn;\n}\n\nif ( oparse(&amp;cda, (text *)\"DROP TABLE FOOBAR\", -1, 0, 2) )\n{\nprintf(\"Drop table failed, Oracle error = %d\\n\", cda.rc);\nreturn;\n}\nprintf(\"Drop table OK.\\n\");\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">Use the following command to link the shared library on Solaris 64-bits.\n            Note the explicit linking of the U4.2 Oracle driver; this was tested with Oracle\n            8.1.7.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104rzp1665703134110_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"rzp1665703134110__codeblock_mc2_vr1_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">cc -g -KPIC -xtarget=ultra -xarch=v9 -G \\\n-I 3gl/include \\\n-I $ORACLE_HOME/rdbms/demo \\\n-o lib/libdroptable.so \\\n-L./lib -luora42 \\\ndroptable.c</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bhu1665703133965.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ugetulda</a><p>Get the address of the Oracle logon data area (LDA) of the first Oracle logon path.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531864\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531864\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ugetuopenflag Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Get the address of the flag that specifies the validity of the Oracle Logon Data Area (LDA). unsigned char* ugetulda (); Copy Parameters None Return Values A pointer to an unsigned char variable that contains the status. Use Oracle only, uora NN (your currently used Oracle driver). Description ugetuopenflag returns a pointer to an unsigned char variable that contains the validity of the Oracle LDA returned by ugetulda . If that variable is 1 (one), the LDA returned by ugetulda is valid; if it is zero, the LDA is invalid and should not be used. Note: You should always call this function before using the LDA returned by ugetulda in Oracle OCI calls. If you fail to do so, you might be using an invalid LDA, which is likely to produce unexpected results. Obviously, you can call this function only when an Oracle driver is available to your application. Example: ugetulda and ugetuopenflag The following 3GL code drops the table FOOBAR from the current Oracle database. Functionally, this might not be the best example, but it is simple and serves to illustrate the use of ugetulda and ugetuopenflag . The routine DROPTABLE can be called, using perform or activate , once the application has logged on to Oracle. Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> #include <stdio.h> #include <ocidem.h> EXPORT void DROPTABLE () { unsigned char *pflg; Lda_Def *plda; Cda_Def cda; pflg = ugetuopenflag(); if ( *pflg != 1 ) { printf(\"No valid LDA\\n\"); return; } plda = (Lda_Def*)ugetulda(); if ( oopen(&cda, plda, NULL, -1, -1, NULL, -1) ) { printf(\"Open cursor failed\\n\"); return; } if ( oparse(&cda, (text *)\"DROP TABLE FOOBAR\", -1, 0, 2) ) { printf(\"Drop table failed, Oracle error = %d\\n\", cda.rc); return; } printf(\"Drop table OK.\\n\"); } Copy Use the following command to link the shared library on Solaris 64-bits. Note the explicit linking of the U4.2 Oracle driver; this was tested with Oracle 8.1.7. Explain this code cc -g -KPIC -xtarget=ultra -xarch=v9 -G \\ -I 3gl/include \\ -I $ORACLE_HOME/rdbms/demo \\ -o lib/libdroptable.so \\ -L./lib -luora42 \\ droptable.c Copy Related Links ugetulda Get the address of the Oracle logon data area (LDA) of the first Oracle logon path. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}